<a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to main content</a>
<header>
<div class="container">
<h1>Canadian Payroll Calculator</h1>
</div>
</header>
<main class="main-content" id="main-content">
<div class="container">
<p>This Canadian Payroll Calculator helps employers and employees calculate their payroll deductions accurately, ensuring compliance with Canadian tax regulations.</p>
<div class="calculator-layout">
<section class="calculator-container" id="calculator">
<h2>Payroll Calculator</h2>
<div class="form-group">
<label for="grossIncome">Gross Income *</label>
<input aria-describedby="grossIncomeError" aria-required="true" class="form-control" id="grossIncome" placeholder="Enter your gross income" type="number"/>
<div class="error-message" id="grossIncomeError" role="alert"></div>
</div>
<div class="form-group">
<label for="province">Province *</label>
<select aria-required="true" class="form-control" id="province">
<option value="ontario">Ontario</option>
<option value="quebec">Quebec</option>
<!-- More provinces can be added here -->
</select>
</div>
<button onclick="calculatePayroll()" type="button">Calculate</button>
</section>
<section class="results-container" id="results">
<h3>Results</h3>
<div class="result-item">
<span class="result-label">Net Income:</span>
<span class="result-value" id="netIncome">$0.00</span>
</div>
<div class="result-item">
<span class="result-label">Total Deductions:</span>
<span class="result-value" id="totalDeductions">$0.00</span>
</div>
</section>
</div>
<section>
<h2>Data Source and Methodology</h2>
<p>Tutti i calcoli si basano rigorosamente sulle formule e sui dati forniti dalla <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/revenue-agency/services/e-services/digital-services-businesses/payroll-deductions-online-calculator.html">Canada Revenue Agency</a>.</p>
</section>
<section>
<h2>The Formula Explained</h2>
<div class="formula-box">
<p>Net Income = Gross Income - (Federal Tax + Provincial Tax + CPP + EI)</p>
</div>
</section>
<section>
<h2>Glossary of Terms</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Gross Income:</strong> The total earnings before deductions.</li>
<li><strong>Net Income:</strong> The amount of income left after deductions.</li>
<li><strong>CPP:</strong> Canada Pension Plan contribution.</li>
<li><strong>EI:</strong> Employment Insurance.</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section>
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<div>
<h3>What is the Canada Pension Plan (CPP)?</h3>
<p>The CPP is a contributory, earnings-related social insurance program. It ensures a basic income for Canadian retirees and their families.</p>
<h3>How often are payroll taxes updated?</h3>
<p>Payroll taxes are typically reviewed and updated annually by the Canadian government.</p>
</div>
</section>
<div class="author-box">
<p>
                    Tool developed by <strong>Ugo Candido</strong>.
                    <br/>
                    Last reviewed for accuracy on: October 2023.
                </p>
</div>
</div>
</main>

<script defer="">
        function calculatePayroll() {
            const grossIncome = parseFloat(document.getElementById('grossIncome').value);
            const province = document.getElementById('province').value;
            let federalTax = 0.15 * grossIncome;
            let provincialTax = 0;
            let cpp = 0.0525 * grossIncome;
            let ei = 0.0158 * grossIncome;

            if (province === 'ontario') {
                provincialTax = 0.0505 * grossIncome;
            } else if (province === 'quebec') {
                provincialTax = 0.15 * grossIncome;
            }

            const totalDeductions = federalTax + provincialTax + cpp + ei;
            const netIncome = grossIncome - totalDeductions;

            document.getElementById('netIncome').textContent = `$${netIncome.toFixed(2)}`;
            document.getElementById('totalDeductions').textContent = `$${totalDeductions.toFixed(2)}`;
        }
    </script>


